# Plan 005 — Audio Synthesis Extensions Integration Test
# Duration: 90 seconds
# Purpose: Exercise all three features introduced in Plan 005:
#   (A) Binaural beat freq_r 7th token — new parser path
#   (B) Harmonic waveforms: square, triangle, sawtooth
#   (C) Noise generators: white, pink, brown
#
# Channel assignments:
#   ch0 = binaural left (200 Hz left, 210 Hz right)
#   ch1 = binaural right workaround channel (210 Hz, silenced at t=10s)
#   ch2 = square-wave isochronic 40 Hz (t=10-20s)
#   ch3 = triangle 220 Hz (t=20-30s)
#   ch4 = sawtooth 440 Hz (t=30-40s)
#   ch5 = white noise continuous (t=40-50s)
#   ch6 = pink noise continuous (t=50-70s)
#   ch7 = brown noise continuous (t=70-90s)

# =============================================================================
# Section 1: Binaural beat (t=0 to t=30s)
# =============================================================================
# Workaround: two separate channels, each mono at their own frequency.
# ch0 hears 200 Hz, ch1 hears 210 Hz. Combined = 10 Hz alpha binaural beat.
# Both are 6-token lines (old format) — exercises backwards compatibility.
A 0 200.0 0 60 0 0
A 0 210.0 0 60 0 1

# At t=5s: re-issue using the new 7th-token syntax (freq_r).
# ch0 alone carries both L (200 Hz) and R (210 Hz) via token 6.
# ch1 is updated to vol=0 so the workaround channel goes silent.
# The listener should hear no glitch — pending-params path fires, no restart click.
A 5000 200.0 0 60 0 0 210.0
A 5000 210.0 0 0 0 1

# Silence both channels at t=30s (end of binaural section)
A 30000 200.0 0 0 0 0
A 30000 210.0 0 0 0 1

# =============================================================================
# Section 2: Square-wave isochronic tone 40 Hz (t=10s to t=20s)
# =============================================================================
# wave_type=1 (AUDIO_WAVE_SQUARE). Hard threshold square at 40 Hz.
# At therapeutic frequencies (<100 Hz) aliasing is inaudible.
# Expected: distinctly harsh, buzzing quality compared to a sine at the same frequency.
A 10000 40.0 0 50 0 2 0.0 1
A 20000 40.0 0 0 0 2 0.0 1

# =============================================================================
# Section 3: Triangle waveform 220 Hz (t=20s to t=30s)
# =============================================================================
# wave_type=2 (AUDIO_WAVE_TRIANGLE). Linear-fold ramp from Q32 phase.
# Expected: softer than square, slightly brighter than sine, gentle mellow tone.
A 20000 220.0 0 50 0 3 0.0 2
A 30000 220.0 0 0 0 3 0.0 2

# =============================================================================
# Section 4: Sawtooth waveform 440 Hz (t=30s to t=40s)
# =============================================================================
# wave_type=3 (AUDIO_WAVE_SAWTOOTH). Signed-cast linear ramp from Q32 phase.
# Expected: rich harmonic content, distinctly buzzy/nasal character.
A 30000 440.0 0 50 0 4 0.0 3
A 40000 440.0 0 0 0 4 0.0 3

# =============================================================================
# Section 5: White noise underlay (t=40s to t=50s)
# =============================================================================
# wave_type=4 (AUDIO_WAVE_NOISE_WHITE). Galois LFSR, polynomial 0xB4BCD35C.
# frequency=0.0: continuous noise, no pulsation/gating modulation.
# Expected: broadband "sh" hiss, wide stereo field (L/R decorrelated seeds).
A 40000 0.0 0 40 0 5 0.0 4
A 50000 0.0 0 0 0 5 0.0 4

# =============================================================================
# Section 6: Pink noise underlay (t=50s to t=70s)
# =============================================================================
# wave_type=5 (AUDIO_WAVE_NOISE_PINK). Kellet 3-pole IIR approximation (-3 dB/oct).
# frequency=0.0: continuous noise, no gating.
# Expected: warmer than white, more bass energy, less high-frequency hiss.
A 50000 0.0 0 40 0 6 0.0 5
A 70000 0.0 0 0 0 6 0.0 5

# =============================================================================
# Section 7: Brown noise underlay (t=70s to t=90s)
# =============================================================================
# wave_type=6 (AUDIO_WAVE_NOISE_BROWN). Leaky integrator (0.998f coeff) of white noise.
# frequency=0.0: continuous noise, no gating.
# Expected: deep low-frequency rumble, dominated by bass, almost no high-frequency content.
A 70000 0.0 0 40 0 7 0.0 6
A 90000 0.0 0 0 0 7 0.0 6
